tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,
review:
A friend recommended Dr. Jasleen to us. We first visited her clinic when we conceived. She was kind and polite, hence, we continued with her for pregnancy and delivery.

She is friendly, straightforward and professional in her approach and is quite approachable, even when we couldn't reach her on the phone due to OPD hours she would always call back and resolve our queries. She guided and made delivery plan with us and always encouraged us to go for a natural birth. She patiently waited for about 16 hours when we tried to induce labour but when that didn't work she advised c-section and counselled us both about the pros and cons, she also fiercely clashed with the hospital authorities to get us into OT for the surgery at the earliest as it was an emergency and we didn't plan for a c-section.

When things were not working in our favour, she made sure that we remain positive and worked around solution  . 
She remained connected with us during labour, visited us in the hospital during wee hours pre and post delivery. We cannot thank her enough for her care and support.

We are forever grateful to Dr. Jasleen for bringing our beautiful daughter in to this world.

review:
My experience with Dr.Jasleen from Gurgaon to Delhi.

Went to Dr. Jasleen from 4th Month of 2nd Pregnancy after changing 4 gynecologists , with lots of health issues.
  
She is so friendly that while telling your problem she will listen it as your elder sister but give you strict instructions as a super specialist doctor, she was very fast in understanding & finding the solution to our odd issues .
She will Motivate you to do your best as a couple to make your pregnancy healthy.
She Motivated us and respected our contribution of a healthy natural diet with the Issue of Thelesemia Minor . My HB was always less than 8, but only with her motivation we made it to 11 till the time of delivery.
I never ever even thought of reaching this level without loading myself with medication .
I just want to thank her a 1000 time for so many issues being solved by her.
Iam even sorry for some of my silly talks. 
 
The Biggest thing in this doctor is true care for her patients , I felt good not only physically but she made me mentally strong.

I will always respect you.
Will Never forget your contribution in my life.

First time parents are always a little impatient and so were we. In fact, we still are.

I remember that after long research on internet in corona Days and talking to many people we came across your name through practo and in our first meeting we saw something in you- you are so much caring & professional.

In corona early stage when doctor's are not ready to meet. In that crucial time we came across to Dr. Jasleen who listen our whole problem & call us same day to meet.I really appreciate that.

During the 9 months span we asked many questions, called you many times(day & night) but almost every time you help us and you were always polite. We irritated you as well by repeating same questions from different ways but as I said earlier we as first time parents are impatient.

We always thank guru ji who bless us with really nice doctor. Thank you ma'am very much for giving us healthy baby and watching over the health of the mother as well.

To conclude:

Pre (Before Delivery) We treated you as our Family Doctor

Post (After Delivery) - We still think you are our Family doctor

Future - You will always remain our family doctor & friend too.

review:
I consulted Doctor Jasleen for my first pregnancy and she successfully delivered my baby girl in September via cesarean section in manipal hospital. All through my stay she visited twice a day to get the updates on my health. Even after operation she guided me throughout for my health related issues
I am thankful to her for making my pregnancy and post partum journey beautiful.

She is a great gynaecologist because of the following reasons:
1. She would listen to all your concerns and clear them very patiently
I used to make a list of questions and ask her in my routine visits - she always answered my queries and cleared my doubts
2. She would explain all the issues in detail
I got the issue of cholastasis towards the end of my pregnancy so she suggested two weeks early delivery 
3. She will not get the unnecessary tests done
I got all my routine ultrasounds done- no extra xrays ultrasounds or blood tests were prescribed
4. She is very approachable - in person and on calls
I used to visit her routinely in the gap of one month and all my visits were very fruitful and if i had doubts or any concerns in between the visits i used to call her and discuss.

Thanks Doctor Jasleen for your guidance üòä

review:
We are proud parents of a beautiful baby girl born 2 days ago and the whole experience beginning from the first ultrasound has been just amazing, all thanks to Dr Jasleen. She made sure everything went smoothly with regular follow-ups and also being available on phone/whatsapp when needed, she also answered our naive questions patiently for us to-be-first-time-parents :). When pains started we simply followed her advice because I knew my wife couldn't be in more safe hands. The doctor came to the hospital at 3am in the night for delivery and also expertly handled some complication at that odd hour, I am so thankful for that. Dr Jasleen had been encouraging my wife to go for a normal delivery and it was indeed a successful normal delivery!

I have never seen a medical professional in my life with such a perfect blend of experience, skills, warmth, patience and dedication towards her work. My wife is usually nervous around hospitals and doctors, but with Dr Jasleen she developed a friendly bond and that speaks volumes about her caring nature towards her patients and making them feel comfortable. I would strongly recommend Dr Jasleen to my friends/family because she is a thorough professional and a very nice person.

review: Doctor is nice but there are some problems regarding the system of clinic. No use of taking a appointment if someone who take appointment of late time and come before time they send them in first and the person who came on time have to wait for 40-50 mins. After seeing the dr. i paid fees and asked will i be charged for showing test reports next time they said no this fees include that. Due to some reasons i came after 8-9 days with reports then they asked me to pay fees. according to them this report session only applicable for 5 days. so why the receptionist didn't mention when i asked her about the reports. is this the way to charge extra fees from patients.
reply_text: Sir my apologies that u had to wait for 40 minutes. It does not happen always as some days r busy. I was not aware of this issue earlier. As for the consultation taken, in every clinic full consultation is taken if a patient visits after a certain tym period.  1 consultation is not valid for the whole month. If doctor is addressing ur issues n writing mds, fees is taken. There is no extra fees taken from patients. Fees is not taken for a period of 6 days if only reports r seen n no mds written thereafter. We charge for our treatment n nobody gives free treatment.
